\f0\fs24 \cf0 1) Raw source used\
- It reads the column cosine-similarity-self-consistency-all-repeats from aggregate_df.\
- From each row, it pulls every cosine point at turn level across:\
  - all repeats\
  - both agents (alpha and beta)\
  - all debate turns\
\
So each turn-level cosine value is one data point.\
\
2) What is consolidated\
- Scenarios included: faculty_manuscript_submission, promotion_committee, ngo_climate_endorsement.\
- Incentive type is collapsed (historical + future together).\
- Only incentive direction is kept for plotting:\
  - negative\
  - positive\
- Baseline rows (None/None) are not plotted as violins; they are used only for normalization.\
\
3) How normalization is computed\
- For each (model, scenario), a baseline mean is computed from baseline rows only (direction=None and type=None), pooling all repeats, turns, and both agents for that same model+scenario.\
- Each plotted point is then:\
  ratio = cosine_point / baseline_mean_for_that_model_and_scenario\
\
So ratio=1 means \'93equal to that model+scenario\'92s own baseline average.\'94\
\
4) What each violin contains\
- X-axis is model.\
- For each model, there are 2 violins:\
  - left: negative (persona-reinforcing)\
  - right: positive (alignment-inducing)\
- Each violin contains all normalized turn-level ratio points for that model and that direction, across all 3 scenarios and both incentive types.\
\
5) What \'93average\'94 is shown on the plot\
- Median is removed.\
- The marker/short line inside each violin is the arithmetic mean of all points in that violin.\
\
6) Axis and styling\
- Y-axis is set to the global min and global max of all plotted ratio points.\
- Color encodes model.\
- Hatch encodes direction (negative vs positive).\
\
7) What is saved\
- PDF figure.\
- A raw data CSV with the exact records used to build violins, including:\
  model_raw, model, scenario_id, direction, incentive_type, repeat, agent, turn, value, pair_baseline_mean, ratio.\
\
8) Diagnostics table (\'93Hypothesis check\'85\'94)\
- Uses the same plotted ratio points.\
- For each model and overall, it computes:\
  - n_negative, n_positive\
  - mean_negative, mean_positive\
  - delta = mean_negative - mean_positive\
  - pct_negative_gt1, pct_positive_gt1\
  - bootstrap 95% CI for each mean and for delta (resampling).\
- supports_expectation is True only if:\
  mean_negative >= 1, mean_positive <= 1, and delta > 0.}